ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How often do you and your partner have minor disagreements
Notes: 1= Once a year or less; 2= Every 4 - 6 months; 3= Every 2 - 3 months; 4= Once or twice a month; 5= Once or twice a week; 6= Just about every day; 999= NA/NK/missing

ElementDescription: How often do you and your partner have major disagreements
Notes: 1= Once a year or less; 2= Every 4 - 6 months; 3= Every 2 - 3 months; 4= Once or twice a month; 5= Once or twice a week; 6= Just about every day; 999= NA/NK/missing

How satisfied are you with the strategies that you have for resolving your conflicts
Notes: 1=Very staisfied; 2=works OK most of the time; 3=works sometimes but could be better; 4=mostly dissatisfied; 5= extremely dissatisfied

ElementDescription: "Overall, how happy are you with this relationship"
Notes: 1=extremely unhappy; 2=fairly unhappy; 3=a little unhappy; 4=a little happy; 5=fairly happy; 6=extremely happy; 7 =perfect

ElementDescription: Frequency: sum of items 1 (minor disagreements) and 2 (major disagreements)
Severity: average rating for Degree of Problem for 21 content areas (1-21)
Resolution score
Notes: Weight frequency scores by resolution quality, and then sum. Items 1,2,3 x 2; Items 4,5 x 1; Items 6-13 x -2; 999=NA/NK/missing

ElementDescription: Efficacy: average rating of % of time resolved for 21 content areas (1-21)
Dimensions of Conflict Strategies: Collaboration: items: 13, 15, 14, 12, 9, 10, 11. Total (me + partner)
Dimensions of Conflict Strategies: Avoidance  Capitulation: items: 23, 22, 20, 6, 18, 19, 21. Total (me + partner)
Dimensions of Conflict Strategies: Stalemate- items: 1, 5, 3, 2, 4, 8, 16, 7.  Total (me + partner)

Dimensions of Conflict Strategies: Physical Aggression: items: 36, 41, 39, 40, 35, 7, 38. Total (me + partner)
Dimensions of Conflict Strategies: Child Involvement: items: 45, 46, 24, 25, 26. Total (me + partner)
